Problem Statement: Tic-Tac-Toe

Design a Tic-Tac-Toe game that allows two players to play on an n × n board.

Requirements:
	1.	The game is played by two players, taking turns.
	2.	Players place their symbol (X or O) on the board.
	3.	A move is valid only if the selected cell is empty.
	4.	After each move, determine if the player has won the game.
	5.	A player wins if they fill an entire row, column, or diagonal.
	6.	If all cells are filled and no player wins, the game is a draw.
	7.	The system should support:
	•	move(row, col, player) → place the player’s mark
	•	Return:
	•	0 → no winner yet
	•	1 → player 1 wins
	•	2 → player 2 wins

Constraints:
	•	Board size n should be configurable.
	•	Each move operation should ideally run in O(1) time.